        'Ask a modern coach where matches are won and lost, and many will point not to settled possession but to transitions — the brief, chaotic moments immediately after the ball changes hands. In those few seconds, defences are disorganised and space appears, and a large share of goals are created or conceded. Understanding transitions is understanding the modern game.',
