        'One of football’s most intriguing tactical ideas is the false nine — a player who lines up as the central striker but does not behave like one. Instead of leading the line and staying high, this forward drops away from goal into midfield, creating a puzzle defenders struggle to solve. It is a clever, counterintuitive concept worth understanding.',
